# Database Connection Walkthrough

This document outlines the modifications made to connect the backend application to the PostgreSQL database, validate credentials at startup, auto-initialize the schema if needed, and run a health check.

## Changes Made

### Configuration and DB Utilities

#### [NEW] [db.config.js](file:///d:/AIML_learning_Projects/app-Org-EventManager/backend/src/configs/db.config.js)
- Established structured validation of all database connection parameters from `.env`.
- Explicitly checks for missing environment variables and throws clear error messages.
- Parses and type-casts numeric pool limits.

#### [MODIFY] [db.js](file:///d:/AIML_learning_Projects/app-Org-EventManager/backend/database/db.js)
- Replaced direct `process.env` lookups with the validated parameters from `db.config.js`.
- Implemented `initializeDatabase()` utility which:
  1. Tests connectivity to the database.
  2. Queries public schema tables.
  3. If 0 tables are found, automatically reads and executes [schema.sql](file:///d:/AIML_learning_Projects/app-Org-EventManager/backend/database/schema.sql).

### Express Application Server

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///d:/AIML_learning_Projects/app-Org-EventManager/backend/src/server.js)
- Integrated Express application setup with JSON parser and CORS middlewares.
- Added database connection and initialization call at startup (with Fail-Fast mechanism).
- Implemented a `/api/health` endpoint returning database connection health dynamically.

